@ September 13, 2017

Good day to you all,

Today brings antivirus to your web proxy via plugins as promised in the
last release announcement.  Please note that we have updated the
documentation on those subjects, something you will see with increasing
frequency from now on.

Here are the full patch notes:

o system: make log file views adapt to log format to fix date display
o system: removed m0n0wall/pfSense config migration code
o reporting: traffic graph mini-graph additions (contributed by Jeffrey Gentes)
o firewall: align NAT target port to destination port when creating a new entry
o firewall: remove spurious filter reload page
o firewall: wrong double-encode in schedule descriptions
o firewall: naturally order settings menu
o firmware: fix ALLOW_RISKY_MAJOR_UPGRADE cron job parameter
o firmware: add new trusted fingerprint key for upcoming rotation
o firmware: ABI auto-append on custom flavour entry without multiple directories
o captive portal: small UX tweaks for dialogs and spacing
o intrusion detection: selectable home networks as advanced option
o intrusion detection: missing gzip decode on download
o unbound: restart on new WAN IP if explicit interface matches
o web proxy: log name now starts with a module name
o rc: clear /var/run contents on bootup
o ui: improved PHP 7.1 compatibility for static pages
o ui: updated nvd3 to version 1.8.5-dev
o ui: allow runtime bootgrid translation (contributed by Fabian Franz)
o plugins: migrate plugin models on install
o plugins: only restart configd once on reinstall
o plugins: os-acme-client 1.10[1] (contributed by Frank Wall)
o plugins: os-clamav 1.0[2] (contributed by Michael Muenz)
o plugins: os-c-icap 1.0[3] (contributed by Michael Muenz)
